.TH "aio_port_set_volume" 9 "aio_port_set_volume" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aio_port_set_volume \- set volume of AIO port block
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" aio_port_set_volume
.BI "(struct uniphier_aio_sub *sub "  ","
.BI "int vol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sub" 12
the AIO substream pointer
.IP "vol" 12
target volume, range is 0x0000 - 0xffff.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Change digital volume and perfome fade-out/fade-in effect for specified
output slot of port. Gained PCM value can calculate as the following:
Gained = Original * vol / 0x4000
